# Agent Workflow Rules (React Native Vibe Engineering)

## Agent Boundaries

### Agent 00: Figma Analyzer
- **Does:** Accept Figma URL + Mobile Frame name, use Figma MCP to extract specs (mobile only), save to `.cursor/cache/figma-specs-{feature}.md`. Extract hierarchy, measurements, colors, typography, spacing; map to React Native (ColorCode, FONTS). When icons/vectors are present, export required SVGs (via Figma MCP export or Figma REST API with `FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN`) to `.cursor/cache/figma-svgs/{feature}/` so development can use them directly.
- **Setup:** Set `FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN` in **`.env`** in the project root (never `.env.local` or `.env.example`; never commit the token). See agent-00-figma-analyzer.md for details.
- **Does not:** Create PRD, write code, or proceed to next agent automatically.
- **Stops when:** Specs file is saved. Invoke: `@figma-analyzer` with Feature name, Mobile URL + Frame, Section.

### Agent 01: Planning Agent
- **Does:** Read Figma specs or prompt, create PRD with communication history, save to `.cursor/logs/prd-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Write code or run tests.
- **Stops when:** PRD is saved. Invoke: `@planning-agent` with prompt or path to specs.

### Agent 02: Coding Agent
- **Does:** Read PRD, load rules/skills (incl. **`ui-qa-checklist.mdc`**), implement code, validate static UI QA in coding log, update coding log, run lint/validation.
- **Does not:** Create PRD or run E2E tests.
- **Stops when:** Code is implemented and log updated. Invoke: `@coding-agent` with PRD path.

### Agent 03: Documentation Agent
- **Does:** Add JSDoc, file headers, inline comments.
- **Does not:** Change logic or add features.
- **Stops when:** Documentation added. Invoke: `@documentation-agent`.

### Agent 04: Fixing Agent
- **Does:** Fix issues from user prompt; read code/coding log, apply fixes, save fixing log to `.cursor/logs/fixing/fixing-{feature}.md`. When testing is requested: require test-cases file (`.cursor/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md`) and testing target (iOS Simulator / Android Emulator); run Jest (and E2E via Detox/Maestro if configured), track results by test case ID and priority, fix simple failures, re-run failed tests, document in same fixing log.
- **Does not:** Create PRD or implement new features.
- **Stops when:** Fixes applied and log updated (and tests run + results documented if test-and-fix). Invoke: `@fixing-agent` with feature name or "Test {feature}" + testing target. Test cases template: `.cursor/rules/log-templates/test-cases-template.md`. **E2E (Detox):** config `.detoxrc.js`, specs `e2e/**/*.e2e.js`, commands `npm run e2e:ios` / `e2e:android`; see `docs/DETOX-INTEGRATION.md` and `.cursor/rules/detox-testing.mdc`.

### Agent 05: Code Scanning Agent
- **Does:** Run quality checklist, run ESLint (and SonarQube if configured), document findings, save report to `.cursor/logs/code-scanning/`.
- **Does not:** Fix code.
- **Stops when:** Report saved. Invoke: `@code-scanning-agent`.

### Agent 06: Vulnerability Agent
- **Does:** Run npm audit (and Snyk if configured), categorize by severity (P1–P4), document prioritized remediation, save report to `.cursor/logs/vulnerability/`.
- **Does not:** Apply fixes.
- **Stops when:** Report saved. Invoke: `@vulnerability-agent`.

### Agent 07: PR Orchestrator Agent
- **Does:** Collect PRD, coding log, fixing log, scans; generate PR document.
- **Does not:** Submit or merge PR.
- **Stops when:** PR document saved. Invoke: `@pr-orchestrator-agent`.

### Agent 08: Project Scaffold Agent
- **Does:** Create a new React Native project with **given app name** and **sample folder structure with boilerplate**. Scaffolds src/ (api, lib, components/layouts, components/widgets, constants, hooks, screens, store, utility), Root.js, AppRouteConfig.js, path aliases, COLORS/fonts/commonStyles, one sample screen (Home), one store slice (Common), **`.env`** (only env file — no `.env.local` / `.env.example`), the **dependency-free fetch client** (`src/lib/fetch-client.ts`, axios-free) via `node .cursor/scripts/setup-fetch.js`, the **`useForm` hook**, and **error pages** (Connection Lost + Unauthorized + NetworkGate + NetInfo) via `node .cursor/scripts/setup-error-pages.js`. **No axios.** Saves log to `.cursor/logs/project-scaffold/project-scaffold-{name}-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Run React Native CLI or npm install; does not create ios/android (user runs CLI separately if needed).
- **Stops when:** All files/folders created and log saved. Invoke: `@project-scaffold-agent` with app name; optional "in new folder" to create sibling directory.

### Agent 09: Prompt Generator Agent
- **Does:** Two modes. (A) Read **business brief** (YAML) and optionally **Figma specs**; generate **prompt for the Planning Agent**; save to `.cursor/cache/prompt-{feature}.md`. (B) Generate **project creation prompt** (React Native + TypeScript + standard boilerplate); save to `.cursor/cache/prompt-project-create-{name}.md` so user or Coding Agent can follow it.
- **Does not:** Create PRD or write code; does not run React Native CLI or Figma MCP (specs must already be in cache from Figma Analyzer if used for mode A).
- **Stops when:** Prompt file is saved. Invoke: `@prompt-generator-agent` with feature name (mode A) or project name + "TypeScript and boilerplate" (mode B).

### Agent 10: Test Case Authoring Agent
- **Does:** Create/manual QA test cases + automated Jest test files for a feature. Bridges the gap between Planning/Coding outputs and Fixing Agent inputs.
- **Does not:** Run Detox E2E tests or fix code.
- **Stops when:** Test cases file and Jest test file created. Invoke: `@testcases-agent` with feature name + PRD/coding log paths.

### Agent 11: Detox Testing Agent
- **Does:** Create Detox E2E test files for a module or entire app (if not created), run Detox tests with screenshot/video capture, generate detailed test reports with artifacts organized in folders (ss, video, test-results.md).
- **Does not:** Fix code, create PRD, or implement features.
- **Stops when:** Tests executed, artifacts organized, test results document generated. Invoke: `@detox-testing-agent` with feature name (or "entire app") + testing target (iOS Simulator / Android Emulator / Both). **E2E (Detox):** config `.detoxrc.js`, specs `e2e/**/*.e2e.js`, commands `npm run e2e:ios` / `e2e:android`; see `docs/DETOX-INTEGRATION.md` and `.cursor/rules/detox-testing.mdc`.

### Agent 12: Pre-PR Validation Agent
- **Does:** Review **only the changed files** (git diff vs base branch; default `main`) and related dependents (for breaking-change context) before a PR. Validates code quality & best practices, folder-structure compliance, React/React Native performance, security/insecure patterns, TypeScript/lint/test (scoped), error handling, **UI static QA (code-level via `ui-qa-checklist.mdc`)**, PR readiness, and potential breaking changes. Runs scoped ESLint/type check/Jest, produces P1/P2/P3 findings and a **READY / NOT READY** verdict. Saves report to `.cursor/logs/pre-pr/pre-pr-{branch-or-feature}-{timestamp}.md`. **Recommendations only — does not modify code.**
- **Does not:** Fix/refactor code, create PRD, implement/scaffold, or create/commit/submit/merge a PR.
- **Stops when:** Report saved and verdict announced. Invoke: `@pre-pr-validation-agent` (optional base branch). Run **before** `@pr-orchestrator-agent`; hand off fixes to `@fixing-agent` / `@coding-agent`.

### Agent 13: useForm Builder Agent
- **Does:** Build or refactor a form using the project's schema-based **`useForm`** hook — RN field handlers (`(name, value)`), `ALERTS` error messages, shared validators in `utility/form-validators`, service-layer submit (`.then()/.catch()`). Detects TypeScript (`.tsx`, typed with `FormSchema`) vs JavaScript. Installs the hook via `node .cursor/scripts/setup-useform.js` if missing. Updates coding log at `.cursor/logs/coding/coding-{feature}.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD, run E2E, or add new form libraries (no Formik/react-hook-form/yup).
- **Stops when:** Form works, tsc/lint pass, coding log updated. Invoke: `@useform-builder-agent` with form name + fields + target path. See `.cursor/rules/useform-validation.mdc`; hook templates in `.cursor/setup/hooks/`.

### Agent 14: Fetch Client Setup Agent
- **Does:** Install and wire the **dependency-free `fetch`-based HTTP client** (axios-free) into a React Native project via `node .cursor/scripts/setup-fetch.js`. Configures `baseURL` + request/response interceptors (auth token, language, 401/403), adds `@lib` path alias, points services at `@lib/fetch-client` (`http`), converts direct axios/raw-fetch usage (incl. uploads → `uploadFile`) to the client, and removes axios from `package.json` where unused. The client mirrors the axios response/error shape so `.then()/.catch()` services keep working. Saves coding log to `.cursor/logs/coding/coding-fetch-client.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD, implement product features, add a third-party HTTP library, or run E2E.
- **Stops when:** Fetch client installed + wired, axios removed where unused, validation passes, log saved. Invoke: `@fetch-client-agent` (optional interceptor needs). See `.cursor/agents/agent-14-fetch-client.md`.

### Agent 15: User Story Test Case Generator
- **Does:** Generate flow-based manual QA test cases from a **user story description** alone (no PRD or coding log required). Saves to `.cursor/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md` with TC-IDs, priorities, flows, testIDs, and Jest/Detox mapping hints for downstream agents.
- **Does not:** Write feature code, run tests, or create Jest/Detox files (use Agent 10 for Jest; Agent 11 for Detox).
- **Stops when:** Test cases file is saved. Invoke: `@user-story-testcases-agent` with feature name + user story text (or path). See `.cursor/agents/agent-15-user-story-testcases.md`.

### Agent 16: Unit Test Analysis Agent
- **Does:** Perform **code-driven** unit test analysis on an implemented React Native screen, component, widget, or layout — inventory inputs/events/validations, build coverage matrix, detect bugs, and generate production-ready Jest + `@testing-library/react-native` tests. Saves report to `.cursor/logs/unit-test-analysis/unit-test-analysis-{feature}-{timestamp}.md` and Jest file to `__tests__/{Feature}.test.js` (unless `analysis only`).
- **Does not:** Fix production code, run Detox E2E, or create PRD.
- **Stops when:** Report saved, Jest file written (unless opted out), and summary posted. Invoke: `@unit-test-analysis-agent` with target name + optional scope. See `.cursor/agents/agent-16-unit-test-analysis.md`.

### Agent 17: npm Audit Auto-Fix Agent
- **Does:** Automatically scan and fix npm vulnerabilities (low, moderate, high, critical) via `node .cursor/scripts/npm-audit-auto-fix.js`. Triggered by the `afterShellExecution` hook after `npm install` / `npm ci`, or invoked manually. Saves report to `.cursor/logs/vulnerability/npm-audit-auto-fix-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Replace Agent 06 documentation-only scans; does not implement product features.
- **Stops when:** Audit + fix run complete and report saved. Invoke: `@npm-audit-auto-fix-agent` (or automatic after `npm install`). See `.cursor/agents/agent-17-npm-audit-auto-fix.md`.

### Agent 18: Error Pages Setup Agent
- **Does:** Install **Connection Lost** and **Unauthorized (Not Authorized)** error pages with global offline handling via `node .cursor/scripts/setup-error-pages.js`. Adds `ConnectionLost` and `Unauthorized` screens, `NetworkGate` (shows Connection Lost when offline), NetInfo-based `useNetworkStatus`, `navigationRef`, `handleUnauthorized`, constants, and `@react-native-community/netinfo`. Wired into `Root.js` and `AppRouteConfig.js`. **Runs automatically during project scaffold (Agent 08).** Saves coding log to `.cursor/logs/coding/coding-error-pages.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD; implement auth/login flow; run `npm install` or `pod install`.
- **Stops when:** Setup complete, wiring verified, log saved. Invoke: `@error-pages-agent`. See `.cursor/agents/agent-18-error-pages.md`.

