## Workflow Sequence

0. **Project Scaffold Agent** (optional) → New RN project with app name + folder structure + boilerplate → `.cursor/logs/project-scaffold/project-scaffold-{name}-{timestamp}.md`
1. **Figma Analyzer** → `.cursor/cache/figma-specs-{feature}.md`
1b. **Business brief** (developer fills) → `.cursor/setup/business-briefs/business-brief-{feature}.yaml`
1c. **Prompt Generator Agent** (optional) → Reads brief + Figma specs → `.cursor/cache/prompt-{feature}.md` (use this as input to Planning Agent)
2. **Planning Agent** → `.cursor/logs/prd-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`
3. **Coding Agent** → Code + `.cursor/logs/coding/coding-{feature}.md`
3b. **useForm Builder Agent** (optional, for forms) → Form built with `useForm` + coding log
3c. **Fetch Client Setup Agent** (optional; scaffold agent already installs it) → `src/lib/fetch-client.ts` wired (axios-free) + `.cursor/logs/coding/coding-fetch-client.md`
3d. **Error Pages Setup Agent** (optional; scaffold agent already installs it) → Connection Lost + Unauthorized pages + NetworkGate + NetInfo → `.cursor/logs/coding/coding-error-pages.md`
4. **Documentation Agent** → Comments + doc log
4a. **User Story Test Case Generator** (optional, story-only — no PRD) → `.cursor/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md`
5. **Test Case Authoring Agent** (optional) → `.cursor/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md` + `__tests__/{Feature}.test.js`
5b. **Unit Test Analysis Agent** (optional, code-driven) → `.cursor/logs/unit-test-analysis/unit-test-analysis-{feature}-{timestamp}.md` + `__tests__/{Feature}.test.js`
6. **Detox Testing Agent** (optional) → Detox E2E tests + artifacts (ss/, video/, test-results.md) at `.cursor/logs/detox-testing/{feature}/{timestamp}/`
7. **Fixing Agent** → Fixes + `.cursor/logs/fixing/fixing-{feature}.md`
8. **Code Scanning Agent** → `.cursor/logs/code-scanning/`
9. **Vulnerability Agent** → `.cursor/logs/vulnerability/`
9b. **npm Audit Auto-Fix Agent** (optional; auto after `npm install`) → `.cursor/logs/vulnerability/npm-audit-auto-fix-{timestamp}.md`
10. **Pre-PR Validation Agent** (before PR) → `.cursor/logs/pre-pr/pre-pr-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`
11. **PR Orchestrator Agent** → `.cursor/logs/pr/pr-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`

Each step requires manual invocation except where an agent explicitly calls another (e.g. Planning does not auto-call Coding).

---

## Invocation (Explicit)

- `@project-scaffold-agent` — App name (e.g. MyApp, FitnessTracker); optional "in new folder" — Creates project with folder structure + boilerplate
- `@prompt-generator-agent` — Feature name (mode A) or project name + "TypeScript and boilerplate" (mode B)
- `@figma-analyzer` — Feature name, Mobile URL + Frame, Section
- `@planning-agent` — Use prompt or path to specs/PRD
- `@coding-agent` — Implement PRD from [prd-file]
- `@useform-builder-agent` — Build/validate a form with the `useForm` hook (form name + fields + target path)
- `@fetch-client-agent` — Install/wire the dependency-free fetch HTTP client (axios-free); replace axios/raw fetch; configure interceptors
- `@error-pages-agent` — Install Connection Lost + Unauthorized error pages with global offline handling (NetInfo + NetworkGate)
- `@documentation-agent` — Document the code
- `@user-story-testcases-agent` — Feature name + user story → manual QA test cases (no PRD required)
- `@testcases-agent` — Feature name + PRD/coding log paths — Creates test cases + Jest tests
- `@unit-test-analysis-agent` — Target screen/component name — Code-driven analysis + Jest tests + bug report
- `@detox-testing-agent` — Feature name (or "entire app") + testing target (iOS Simulator / Android Emulator / Both) — Creates Detox tests, runs E2E, captures screenshots/videos, generates reports
- `@fixing-agent` — Feature name or description of what to fix
- `@code-scanning-agent` — Scan quality for [feature]
- `@vulnerability-agent` — Scan security
- `@npm-audit-auto-fix-agent` — Auto-fix npm vulnerabilities (also runs after `npm install` via hook)
- `@pre-pr-validation-agent` — Validate only changed files before a PR (quality, structure, performance, security, TS/lint/test, PR readiness, breaking changes) + READY/NOT READY verdict
- `@pr-orchestrator-agent` — Create PR for [feature]

One agent, one task, one stop. Human approval at each step.
